From 95923f25cf1939138319b06edbcddbca542ab5d4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 11:49:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] creatures: unwrap framework signal envelope; stores: dispatch
 real CRUD

The namespace creatures (chain, invites, pc, storage, stores) previously
parsed the wasm input as a flat {path, payload, creatureId, spaceId}, but
the host's runVm payload is a wrapped {user, store, action, data, entityId}
envelope with the actual {action, payload} buried one or two JSON layers
deep. As a result, p.Path was always empty and the per-action dispatch
never fired.

* All five namespace creatures now use unwrapSignal() to peel the wrapper
  layers and surface the user-supplied action + payload.
* stores creature dispatches create/update/delete/get/list to the matching
  host ops (createStore, updateStore, deleteStore, getStore, listStores)
  so signalMiniapp("stores", "create", payload) actually persists a Store.
* build-all.sh: one-shot tinygo build of every namespace + endpoint
  creature to ./wasm/ for deployment via the decillion CLI.
